description.narrative: UNICEF helped the Finance Ministry build national and subnational capacity on budget planning, reaching 240 participants and completing prior efforts to cover the country's 13 municipalities. It also targeted parliamentarians with a budget brief advocating for investing in children in the 2020 State budget. The budget is still under debate, amidst concern over fiscal sustainability. UNICEF and UNDP partnered to assist the Government in exploring the feasibility of a unique ID system to strengthen the right to a legal identity and better manage service delivery. Despite enthusiasm from some ministries, further advocacy is needed to move this project forward. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/02/2020
